<comment type="function">
<text evidence="2 3 4">Catalyzes the dephosphorylation of 5-amino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribitylamino)uracil, and thus could be involved in the riboflavin biosynthesis pathway (PubMed:24123841). Is also able to dephosphorylate flavin mononucleotide (FMN) and other phosphoric acid esters (PubMed:16990279) (PubMed:24123841). YigB is important for the formation of dormant persister cells (PubMed:18519731).</text>
</comment>
<comment type="catalytic activity">
<reaction evidence="4">
<text>5-amino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribitylamino)uracil + H2O = 5-amino-6-(D-ribitylamino)uracil + phosphate</text>
